1
00:00:44,462 --> 00:00:46,547
<i>♪ Stick it up, mister! ♪</i>

2
00:00:49,049 --> 00:00:51,427
<i>♪ Hear what I say, sir, yeah ♪</i>

3
00:00:54,680 --> 00:00:57,224
<i>♪ Get your hands in the air, sir! ♪</i>

4
00:01:01,353 --> 00:01:05,316
<i>♪ Then you will get
no hurt, mister, no, no, no ♪</i>

5
00:01:05,399 --> 00:01:08,527
<i>♪ I said, yeah ♪</i>

6
00:01:08,611 --> 00:01:11,030
<i>♪ What they say ♪</i>

7
00:01:11,113 --> 00:01:14,158
<i>♪ Don't you hear me say, yeah? ♪</i>

8
00:01:14,241 --> 00:01:17,912
<i>♪ Listen what they say ♪</i>

9
00:01:17,995 --> 00:01:21,040
<i>♪ Do you believe I would take
such a thing with me ♪</i>

10
00:01:21,123 --> 00:01:25,252
<i>♪ And give it to a policeman?
I wouldn't do that ♪</i>

11
00:01:26,962 --> 00:01:29,673
<i>"♪ And if I do that, I would say " Sir ♪</i>

12
00:01:30,216 --> 00:01:32,843
<i>♪ "Come on and put the charge on me" ♪</i>

13
00:01:32,927 --> 00:01:35,888
<i>♪ I wouldn't do that, oh ♪</i>

14
00:01:35,971 --> 00:01:37,807
<i>♪ I wouldn't do that ♪</i>

15
00:01:39,225 --> 00:01:41,727
<i>♪ I'm not a fool to hurt myself ♪</i>

16
00:01:41,811 --> 00:01:45,105
<i>♪ So I was innocent
of what they done to me ♪</i>

17
00:01:45,189 --> 00:01:47,817
<i>♪ They was wrong ♪</i>

18
00:01:47,900 --> 00:01:50,736
<i>♪ They was wrong ♪</i>

19
00:01:50,820 --> 00:01:53,864
<i>♪ Give it to me one time ♪</i>

20
00:01:53,948 --> 00:01:57,034
<i>♪ Give it to me two times ♪</i>

21
00:01:57,117 --> 00:02:00,579
<i>♪ Give it to me three times...</i>

22
00:02:00,663 --> 00:02:02,540
This is an abusive work relationship.

23
00:02:02,623 --> 00:02:03,624
Get into character.

24
00:02:03,958 --> 00:02:05,835
My character's gonna murder
your character.

25
00:02:05,918 --> 00:02:07,920
Ah... all right. All right.

26
00:02:09,964 --> 00:02:13,551
Kinda diggin' these wheels
though, right? We could do this.

27
00:02:13,634 --> 00:02:17,888
Get one of these bad boys, drive
across country, me and Cody.

28
00:02:17,972 --> 00:02:19,932
- Someday, I hope.
- And how's he doin'?

29
00:02:20,015 --> 00:02:23,018
You know, keep hoping
that time will do its thing,

30
00:02:23,102 --> 00:02:25,771
but he keeps pulling away.

31
00:02:25,855 --> 00:02:28,607
I had to take his car keys
from him this morning.

32
00:02:28,691 --> 00:02:30,693
Did not go well.

33
00:02:48,210 --> 00:02:50,254
- Idiot!
- Stop!

34
00:02:51,630 --> 00:02:53,090
Yes, finish strong!

35
00:02:53,173 --> 00:02:55,676
- I know him.
- I bring you lunch.

36
00:02:55,759 --> 00:02:58,095
- So smooth.
- Thanks.

37
00:02:58,178 --> 00:03:00,973
- Overcompensating?
- Constantly. Just for you.

38
00:03:01,056 --> 00:03:02,224
- Wow!
- Wow!

39
00:03:02,308 --> 00:03:03,308
What a mess!

40
00:03:03,350 --> 00:03:05,686
Uh... compliments of Mama Padilla.

41
00:03:05,769 --> 00:03:06,770
Ah...

42
00:03:06,854 --> 00:03:08,522
I told her not to make the heavy stuff

43
00:03:08,606 --> 00:03:09,690
when you have a meet...

44
00:03:09,773 --> 00:03:12,151
Just tell her I love them
and thank you very much.

45
00:03:12,234 --> 00:03:13,234
- Hey...
- Hi y'all.

46
00:03:13,277 --> 00:03:16,030
Hello, family. Ooh, cupcakes.

47
00:03:16,113 --> 00:03:18,073
What mood was your dad in this morning?

48
00:03:18,157 --> 00:03:19,909
Shitty. He stole my car keys.

49
00:03:19,992 --> 00:03:21,827
It's not like I have another set though.

50
00:03:21,911 --> 00:03:24,413
You just don't learn.
He's gonna kill you, white boy.

51
00:03:24,496 --> 00:03:26,165
I'll be home before him.

52
00:03:26,248 --> 00:03:28,709
But he did say he'd be working late, so...

53
00:03:28,792 --> 00:03:30,210
My mom seems torqued up.

54
00:03:30,294 --> 00:03:32,129
I think something's going down today.

55
00:03:32,212 --> 00:03:33,797
My mom said a little extra prayer.

56
00:03:33,881 --> 00:03:35,257
She always does before a raid.

57
00:03:35,341 --> 00:03:38,135
Now I'm going to be worried
about this all day.

58
00:03:39,094 --> 00:03:41,138
Guys, they are gonna be fine.

59
00:03:41,221 --> 00:03:43,265
- Yeah.
- All right, they always are.

60
00:03:45,142 --> 00:03:46,894
<i>♪ You can forget all your troubles...</i>

61
00:03:46,977 --> 00:03:49,271
All right, there it is. Let's do it.

62
00:03:49,355 --> 00:03:50,731
Yep.

63
00:03:51,273 --> 00:03:52,650
Showtime.

64
00:03:56,737 --> 00:04:02,534
<i>♪ Just take a walk
down this street ♪</i>

65
00:04:02,618 --> 00:04:05,996
<i>♪ Lots of people you will meet...</i>

66
00:04:06,080 --> 00:04:08,165
Here we go.

67
00:04:13,837 --> 00:04:14,837
- Hey...
- Hey, señor.

68
00:04:14,880 --> 00:04:16,423
- Hey!
- No gas?

69
00:04:16,507 --> 00:04:17,591
No gas.

70
00:04:18,634 --> 00:04:21,428
- Sign says "gas".
<i>- Lo siento, </i>no gas today.

71
00:04:21,512 --> 00:04:24,264
If you don't have any gas,
your sign should say "no gas".

72
00:04:25,015 --> 00:04:26,767
Try down the road, we're all out.

73
00:04:26,850 --> 00:04:29,186
How far down the road?
I gotta use the bathroom.

74
00:04:29,269 --> 00:04:32,439
- Piss on the road.
- I don't have to piss.

75
00:04:32,523 --> 00:04:34,817
I've got a turtle that needs
to be released in the wild.

76
00:04:34,900 --> 00:04:36,735
Know what I mean?

77
00:04:36,819 --> 00:04:39,279
Hey, <i>cabron.</i>

78
00:04:39,363 --> 00:04:41,156
- Easy.
- Better get back in.

79
00:04:41,240 --> 00:04:44,118
I just had to use the bathroom.
That's all. Take it easy.

80
00:04:46,412 --> 00:04:48,914
Gotcha. Nice job, Wash.

81
00:04:52,001 --> 00:04:53,711
It's go time.

82
00:04:57,923 --> 00:04:59,299
Ooh...

83
00:04:59,383 --> 00:05:02,553
Ah man, you put my favourite shirt on.

84
00:05:02,636 --> 00:05:04,054
Just for you, Padilla.

85
00:05:04,138 --> 00:05:06,557
- Home in time for dinner, right?
- Hell, yeah!

86
00:05:06,640 --> 00:05:07,975
Hey guys.

87
00:05:08,058 --> 00:05:10,436
Just in case, let's keep
our phones on vibrate, okay?

88
00:05:10,519 --> 00:05:12,438
- Yeah.
- Sure.

89
00:05:12,521 --> 00:05:14,398
Hey, have fun in AP Calculus, nerd.

90
00:05:14,481 --> 00:05:16,525
- Oh, you know I will.
- Must be nice.

91
00:05:16,608 --> 00:05:19,361
- Free ride to Princeton.
- Bye.

92
00:05:23,741 --> 00:05:25,617
Hey, you're the new girl, right?

93
00:05:25,701 --> 00:05:28,078
Yeah, thanks for reminding me.

94
00:05:28,162 --> 00:05:29,913
- I'm Cody.
- Teresa.

95
00:05:29,997 --> 00:05:33,333
I think you're in my chem class,
we should like, study some time.

96
00:05:33,417 --> 00:05:36,879
I'm actually kind of hoping
to pass that class. But thanks.

97
00:05:39,506 --> 00:05:42,384
I'm gonna tell him. Nice... Strike out!

98
00:05:42,468 --> 00:05:44,219
It wasn't a strike out necessarily.

99
00:05:44,303 --> 00:05:46,889
More like a... scouting report.

100
00:05:46,972 --> 00:05:48,557
She don't know what she's missing.

101
00:05:48,640 --> 00:05:51,435
- I'll go on a date with you.
- All right.

102
00:05:57,524 --> 00:05:59,109
Lower your weapon.

103
00:06:01,236 --> 00:06:02,237
Grenade!

104
00:06:04,865 --> 00:06:06,450
Move in.

105
00:06:38,816 --> 00:06:40,442
Here!

106
00:06:49,827 --> 00:06:51,120
- Clear.
- Clear.

107
00:06:57,835 --> 00:06:59,795
All the way to Mexico, huh, baby?

108
00:07:00,504 --> 00:07:02,798
Deep and dirty, like your mom.

109
00:07:25,362 --> 00:07:27,990
The DEA didn't get lucky.

110
00:07:28,073 --> 00:07:29,283
There's a rat!

111
00:07:30,492 --> 00:07:32,536
And Benito will get rid of it!

112
00:07:33,203 --> 00:07:34,538
DEA!

113
00:07:41,378 --> 00:07:43,255
Clear.

114
00:07:47,968 --> 00:07:49,469
Stop!

115
00:07:51,263 --> 00:07:53,974
Shit, it's wired.
It's wired. Go! Go back. Go!

116
00:07:54,057 --> 00:07:55,100
Shit!

117
00:07:59,563 --> 00:08:01,982
Move down to the left, old man!

118
00:08:03,066 --> 00:08:04,443
Go, go, go, go, go.

119
00:08:04,526 --> 00:08:05,903
Move, move.

120
00:08:05,986 --> 00:08:07,529
Come on!

121
00:08:10,908 --> 00:08:12,284
Come on!

122
00:08:25,047 --> 00:08:26,590
Just move!

123
00:08:37,559 --> 00:08:39,144
Go, go, go.

124
00:08:41,772 --> 00:08:42,940
Everyone out!

125
00:08:43,023 --> 00:08:44,524
Let's go!

126
00:08:45,692 --> 00:08:47,694
Go, go, go, go, go!

127
00:08:48,987 --> 00:08:50,697
Aargh!

128
00:08:59,164 --> 00:09:00,540
Shit, was tighter than a

129
00:09:05,629 --> 00:09:06,964
Sniper! Sniper.

130
00:09:07,047 --> 00:09:10,300
Across the border! Across the border!

131
00:09:10,968 --> 00:09:12,219
Man down!

132
00:09:13,262 --> 00:09:15,013
Manny.

133
00:09:16,932 --> 00:09:18,392
Shoot. Shoot!

134
00:09:21,687 --> 00:09:23,605
Go! Go! Come on!

135
00:09:25,816 --> 00:09:27,109
Go!

136
00:09:27,818 --> 00:09:30,570
Can Jesse Padilla
please come to the office?

137
00:09:58,307 --> 00:10:00,267
What happened?

138
00:11:07,417 --> 00:11:09,336
I didn't say bye to him this morning.

139
00:11:09,419 --> 00:11:10,587
I'm sorry.

140
00:11:12,589 --> 00:11:13,965
Jesse...

141
00:11:14,841 --> 00:11:17,010
I don't know what to do.

142
00:11:59,219 --> 00:12:01,930
Damn it, Cody. Really?
Been texting you for hours.

143
00:12:02,013 --> 00:12:04,474
What are you talking about?
I told you where I was going.

144
00:12:04,558 --> 00:12:05,809
That's not the point.

145
00:12:05,892 --> 00:12:07,686
This is not the night to ghost me.

146
00:12:08,937 --> 00:12:10,981
Jesus Christ, Dad. Are you okay?

147
00:12:11,064 --> 00:12:12,816
- Yeah.
- What happened?

148
00:12:12,899 --> 00:12:14,734
Nothing, I'm fine. Okay? Except...

149
00:12:14,818 --> 00:12:16,445
I've been worried sick about you,

150
00:12:16,528 --> 00:12:18,155
because you can't bother to text?

151
00:12:18,238 --> 00:12:21,283
I was focused on Jesse, okay?
He's a wreck.

152
00:12:21,366 --> 00:12:22,993
It's just not safe right now.

153
00:12:23,076 --> 00:12:25,704
We can't keep doing this. Okay?

154
00:12:25,787 --> 00:12:28,498
I'm 18 now. You gotta loosen
the leash a little bit.

155
00:12:28,582 --> 00:12:30,208
I just need you to be more careful.

156
00:12:30,292 --> 00:12:32,669
- If I text, you text me back.
- Okay, I'm sorry.

157
00:12:32,752 --> 00:12:34,796
I should have texted you back.

158
00:12:35,839 --> 00:12:38,550
Look... I know it's gonna be hard,

159
00:12:38,633 --> 00:12:40,552
but I was talking with the other parents.

160
00:12:41,386 --> 00:12:43,638
We don't think you guys
should hang out for a while.

161
00:12:43,722 --> 00:12:45,199
- Are you serious?
- Just for a while.

162
00:12:45,223 --> 00:12:46,433
We get the drill.

163
00:12:46,516 --> 00:12:48,244
There's other people around,
we don't say anything.

164
00:12:48,268 --> 00:12:52,189
You know, right now
it's just a risk. Okay?

165
00:12:52,272 --> 00:12:54,858
- Yeah.
- Thanks.

166
00:12:54,941 --> 00:12:57,152
Come on. Let me make something to eat.

167
00:12:57,986 --> 00:12:59,905
I already ate.

168
00:13:07,704 --> 00:13:10,290
Manny was the best of us.

169
00:13:14,336 --> 00:13:17,172
A man who cared deeply
about his community

170
00:13:19,341 --> 00:13:21,134
his friends...

171
00:13:22,886 --> 00:13:24,638
Most of all, his family.

172
00:13:24,721 --> 00:13:26,932
A loving husband to his wife, Lucy.

173
00:13:27,849 --> 00:13:29,935
I'm so proud of his son, Jesse.

174
00:13:31,436 --> 00:13:34,397
He was our North Star

175
00:13:34,481 --> 00:13:36,983
and we always tried to follow his example.

176
00:14:02,759 --> 00:14:06,846
It seems
that we have a very big problem.

177
00:14:06,930 --> 00:14:08,390
In this house.

178
00:14:10,016 --> 00:14:13,895
And it seems we have an infestation...

179
00:14:15,230 --> 00:14:20,318
Rats. Rats. Rats.

180
00:14:24,698 --> 00:14:28,743
A rat told the DEA

181
00:14:28,827 --> 00:14:30,745
about our tunnel.

182
00:14:31,705 --> 00:14:33,540
And they stole our cheese.

183
00:14:34,165 --> 00:14:35,959
So where's our cheese, huh?

184
00:14:37,127 --> 00:14:38,587
Where's our cheese?

185
00:14:40,463 --> 00:14:42,340
Vasquez killed a pig for me.

186
00:14:44,342 --> 00:14:45,885
So he's clean.

187
00:14:46,720 --> 00:14:48,763
But all you idiots...

188
00:14:50,265 --> 00:14:52,434
How many rats are there here?

189
00:14:55,604 --> 00:14:57,564
Who's the rat, <i>cabrones?</i>

190
00:15:06,323 --> 00:15:08,241
Was it you, my friend?

191
00:15:08,992 --> 00:15:10,452
Are you the rat?

192
00:15:10,535 --> 00:15:13,079
No, boss. No, never.

193
00:15:17,083 --> 00:15:18,918
Kill him.

194
00:15:20,170 --> 00:15:22,088
I know he's your cousin.

195
00:15:23,048 --> 00:15:25,634
I gave you your first job
together, remember?

196
00:15:25,717 --> 00:15:27,093
When you were kids.

197
00:15:41,316 --> 00:15:43,568
No, cousin, don't kill me.

198
00:15:43,652 --> 00:15:45,362
Don't kill me.

199
00:15:52,994 --> 00:15:57,332
If we find the rats,
they'll lead us to the pigs!

200
00:16:01,920 --> 00:16:04,464
Rats and pigs, really?

201
00:16:04,547 --> 00:16:06,049
Quite a performance.

202
00:16:06,132 --> 00:16:07,509
You feel better now?

203
00:16:07,592 --> 00:16:10,428
- He's improved, no?
- No, he hasn't.

204
00:16:13,348 --> 00:16:14,849
This is no way to live.

205
00:16:14,933 --> 00:16:17,018
He's survived much worse.

206
00:16:17,102 --> 00:16:18,728
You shouldn't even be here.

207
00:16:18,812 --> 00:16:20,331
Looks like you need the help.

208
00:16:20,355 --> 00:16:22,607
You're helping in El Paso.

209
00:16:22,691 --> 00:16:24,359
You lost an entire tunnel.

210
00:16:24,442 --> 00:16:26,111
Months of work for nothing.

211
00:16:26,194 --> 00:16:28,071
What do you think he'd do?

212
00:16:28,154 --> 00:16:30,424
- Flush out the rats.
- Like I'm doing.

213
00:16:30,448 --> 00:16:32,575
Papito operated like a shadow.

214
00:16:33,785 --> 00:16:36,371
The work
you're doing there is vital.

215
00:16:37,455 --> 00:16:38,832
I can only trust you.

216
00:16:46,089 --> 00:16:49,509
Let's get started. We are
having a lab session today.

217
00:16:49,592 --> 00:16:53,430
So everyone, please find
a partner. Don't be shy.

218
00:16:57,267 --> 00:16:58,435
- Me?
- Mm-hm.

219
00:16:58,518 --> 00:17:01,146
When I was little, I used
to blow shit up all the time.

220
00:17:01,229 --> 00:17:03,606
I'm not sure that's the assignment.

221
00:17:03,690 --> 00:17:05,483
The 13 x 100, the smaller one.

222
00:17:05,567 --> 00:17:08,570
Oh, you actually know this?
That wasn't a bullshit?

223
00:17:08,653 --> 00:17:10,989
That was mostly bullshit, but like I said,

224
00:17:11,072 --> 00:17:13,867
when I was younger,
I was like a mad scientist.

225
00:17:13,950 --> 00:17:15,744
- I was a real punk.
- Was?!

226
00:17:16,286 --> 00:17:18,788
How do you like El Paso so far?
Pretty cool, right?

227
00:17:19,247 --> 00:17:21,833
- Please tell me you're kidding.
- Of course.

228
00:17:21,916 --> 00:17:24,210
I am trying to like it.
I mean, I kind of have to.

229
00:17:24,294 --> 00:17:26,504
It's not like we can move back.

230
00:17:26,588 --> 00:17:28,339
I had a whole life in San Antonio.

231
00:17:28,423 --> 00:17:30,633
All my friends are there.

232
00:17:30,717 --> 00:17:32,719
But now I have to start over.

233
00:17:32,802 --> 00:17:34,846
That's gotta be tough. I'm sorry.

234
00:17:35,263 --> 00:17:36,931
Thanks.

235
00:17:37,474 --> 00:17:39,559
At least I have a lab partner.

236
00:17:40,894 --> 00:17:42,771
- Shall we?
- Yeah.

237
00:17:43,104 --> 00:17:45,148
- Cheers!
- Ready?

238
00:17:45,231 --> 00:17:46,649
Yep.

239
00:17:47,567 --> 00:17:49,903
Whoa! Jeez!

240
00:17:49,986 --> 00:17:51,946
Boom... science.

241
00:18:23,520 --> 00:18:25,313
He's clean.

242
00:18:35,323 --> 00:18:38,284
Hi, I'm here
to collect the order. Thanks.

243
00:18:42,622 --> 00:18:44,749
Benito knows it's me.

244
00:18:45,667 --> 00:18:47,752
If he knew it was you,
you wouldn't be here.

245
00:18:48,294 --> 00:18:51,256
I can't do this. I can't help you anymore.

246
00:18:51,339 --> 00:18:53,174
I'm out. I'm sorry.

247
00:18:53,258 --> 00:18:54,592
Then you're out.

248
00:18:54,676 --> 00:18:56,719
That was the deal.

249
00:18:56,803 --> 00:18:59,556
Just give me a few days
to work out witness protection.

250
00:18:59,639 --> 00:19:01,724
- Thank you.
- Any word on the new tunnel?

251
00:19:01,808 --> 00:19:03,184
Not yet.

252
00:19:03,810 --> 00:19:05,728
I heard Benito's sister lives in El Paso.

253
00:19:05,812 --> 00:19:09,107
- I didn't know he had a sister.
- I think her name's Natalia.

254
00:19:09,190 --> 00:19:11,109
I bet she's here under a fake name.

255
00:19:11,192 --> 00:19:13,570
- You know what she's doing here?
- Don't know.

256
00:19:13,653 --> 00:19:16,322
Everything about her,
they keep real quiet.

257
00:19:16,948 --> 00:19:20,118
- Appreciate it, thanks.
- Thanks.

258
00:19:39,178 --> 00:19:40,847
Come on, gentlemen!

259
00:19:46,477 --> 00:19:47,937
Hey, what's going on?

260
00:19:48,021 --> 00:19:50,690
We're not supposed to hang out.

261
00:19:50,773 --> 00:19:53,735
Uh, I am moving
and I have to transfer schools.

262
00:19:53,818 --> 00:19:56,154
What? Like moving away?

263
00:19:56,237 --> 00:19:58,615
We're moving in
with my mom's sister in Abilene,

264
00:19:58,698 --> 00:20:00,033
eight hours away.

265
00:20:00,116 --> 00:20:02,493
It's either that or Spain.
I have grandparents there.

266
00:20:02,577 --> 00:20:03,620
- Oh, man.
- Yeah.

267
00:20:03,703 --> 00:20:06,289
The DEA's death benefits are, um, shit,

268
00:20:06,372 --> 00:20:08,625
as it turns out, and with my dad not here,

269
00:20:08,708 --> 00:20:10,376
we can't afford to stay in the house.

270
00:20:10,460 --> 00:20:13,379
Mom's medical is gonna run out soon.

271
00:20:13,463 --> 00:20:15,465
I don't think I can talk
about that right now.

272
00:20:15,548 --> 00:20:19,218
- It's okay.
- Hey, come here. It's okay.

273
00:20:29,270 --> 00:20:34,400
<i>The news from El Paso and Juárez.</i>

274
00:20:40,823 --> 00:20:43,576
Did you hear Jesse and
his mom are having to move away?

275
00:20:43,660 --> 00:20:46,913
Yeah, I heard. We'll visit. Roadtrip.

276
00:20:46,996 --> 00:20:49,457
Isn't there anything
the DEA can do to help them?

277
00:20:49,540 --> 00:20:51,501
What about all that cash
you seized in the raid?

278
00:20:51,584 --> 00:20:53,628
It goes into our operating budget.

279
00:20:53,711 --> 00:20:55,463
That's how we keep pace with the cartels.

280
00:20:55,546 --> 00:20:57,548
But Jesse's dad died getting that money.

281
00:20:57,632 --> 00:21:00,468
Doesn't the DEA owe the family something?

282
00:21:00,551 --> 00:21:04,222
Yeah, I hear you, bud,
but it's not the way it works.

283
00:21:04,305 --> 00:21:07,767
We're setting up a GoFundMe
for them. We'll do what we can.

284
00:21:07,850 --> 00:21:09,852
So if you die, I get a GoFundMe?

285
00:21:26,327 --> 00:21:28,413
- To Manny.
- Manny.

286
00:21:34,085 --> 00:21:36,087
I always wished
I could be more like Manny.

287
00:21:36,170 --> 00:21:39,132
Really? He wanted to be like you.

288
00:21:39,215 --> 00:21:41,050
- No.
- Yeah.

289
00:21:41,843 --> 00:21:46,347
I don't mean about the job.
Manny was such a great father.

290
00:21:46,431 --> 00:21:49,475
Hey, man. You're a great father.

291
00:21:49,559 --> 00:21:52,645
No, Wendy was the one who
knew how to be there for Cody.

292
00:21:52,729 --> 00:21:55,398
Even after she got sick,

293
00:21:56,607 --> 00:22:00,820
she held us together...
right up till the end.

294
00:22:02,447 --> 00:22:04,157
And now...

295
00:22:05,283 --> 00:22:06,909
Yeah.

296
00:22:06,993 --> 00:22:10,121
I don't know shit, right?
I mean, I don't have kids, but...

297
00:22:12,540 --> 00:22:16,252
You know, Lizzy's been bringing Deni
on the training exercises, right?

298
00:22:16,335 --> 00:22:19,881
Yeah, yeah... She wants Deni to join up.

299
00:22:20,882 --> 00:22:23,217
I don't want Cody anywhere near this job.

300
00:22:23,301 --> 00:22:25,970
Way too cowboy, that kid.
He'll get himself killed.

301
00:22:26,054 --> 00:22:27,764
I know, I hear that, but...

302
00:22:27,847 --> 00:22:32,101
It looks like she's trying to
spend some time with her, right?

303
00:22:32,185 --> 00:22:34,437
No pressure, no agenda.

304
00:22:35,813 --> 00:22:37,940
Things open up.

305
00:22:40,818 --> 00:22:42,695
Wrist control. Grab the wrist.

306
00:22:42,779 --> 00:22:45,364
If they're backing away
from you, go double wrist.

307
00:22:45,448 --> 00:22:47,992
Put your weight on them. Trip them.

308
00:22:48,076 --> 00:22:49,660
There it is.

309
00:22:49,744 --> 00:22:52,872
Another way,
same wrist control, under hook.

310
00:22:52,955 --> 00:22:55,500
Scoot under and drag 'em back.

311
00:22:55,583 --> 00:22:56,959
There it is.

312
00:22:57,043 --> 00:22:58,586
- Hey.
- Hey.

313
00:22:58,669 --> 00:23:00,296
- Cody wrestles, right?
- Yeah.

314
00:23:00,379 --> 00:23:03,299
You want to get him out here.
Throw him around a bit.

315
00:23:03,382 --> 00:23:05,802
- I just want him watching today.
- All right.

316
00:23:05,885 --> 00:23:08,346
Come on, guys.
Let's get on these bags.

317
00:23:12,475 --> 00:23:16,062
<i>♪ Whatever happened to the plans we made ♪</i>

318
00:23:16,145 --> 00:23:19,524
<i>♪ Laying awake after midnight ♪</i>

319
00:23:20,233 --> 00:23:23,069
<i>♪ Oh, I don't want to lose that flame...</i>

320
00:23:25,613 --> 00:23:27,573
Hey. Cody's with me.

321
00:23:27,657 --> 00:23:30,618
<i>- Cody, what's the word?</i>
- Hey Wash. I'm good.

322
00:23:30,701 --> 00:23:33,287
Ray, I just rolled up on
a trap house on the south side.

323
00:23:33,371 --> 00:23:35,331
- Wanna check it out?
- Is it locked down?

324
00:23:35,414 --> 00:23:37,917
Cops have been here for hours.
Nothing to worry about.

325
00:23:38,000 --> 00:23:41,295
What do you say? Want to see a trap house?

326
00:23:42,171 --> 00:23:44,215
Yeah, that'll be cool.

327
00:23:46,425 --> 00:23:51,889
<i>♪ The years go by and somehow
I just can't forget...</i>

328
00:23:54,600 --> 00:23:56,519
There it is.

329
00:24:00,189 --> 00:24:01,816
All right...

330
00:24:03,151 --> 00:24:04,986
- How's it going, Cody?
- Hey. All right.

331
00:24:05,069 --> 00:24:06,279
- Hey.
- Hey.

332
00:24:06,362 --> 00:24:08,364
- How did they bust it?
- It was a tough case.

333
00:24:08,447 --> 00:24:10,158
Tweaker passed out on the sidewalk.

334
00:24:10,241 --> 00:24:11,659
Nobody bothered to bring him in.

335
00:24:11,742 --> 00:24:13,369
A black-and-white was just rolling by.

336
00:24:14,370 --> 00:24:16,455
- Good help's hard to find.
- Yeah.

337
00:24:16,539 --> 00:24:19,083
Welcome to the glamorous life
of dealing drugs.

338
00:24:20,168 --> 00:24:22,837
- I'd say don't touch anything...
- Yeah, no danger of that.

339
00:24:22,920 --> 00:24:24,338
- Anybody talking?
- Nah.

340
00:24:24,422 --> 00:24:26,632
Good soldiers,
nothing on the wiretaps either

341
00:24:26,716 --> 00:24:29,719
but I think there must be
a distribution hub nearby.

342
00:24:29,802 --> 00:24:31,679
Yeah, that'll make sense.

343
00:24:54,327 --> 00:24:56,495
- Wash... Reynolds.
- Yeah.

344
00:25:19,936 --> 00:25:21,176
His sister, Natalia.

345
00:25:21,437 --> 00:25:24,357
PFM has heard the rumour too,
but they got nothing on her.

346
00:25:24,440 --> 00:25:26,651
No files, no photos. Nothing.

347
00:25:26,734 --> 00:25:29,237
Her father could've wiped
her records decades ago.

348
00:25:29,320 --> 00:25:31,906
It's gotta be how
she's getting back and forth.

349
00:25:38,996 --> 00:25:41,624
If she is in El Paso,
she probably has a US passport,

350
00:25:41,707 --> 00:25:43,459
solid identity, all backstopped.

351
00:25:43,542 --> 00:25:44,877
So we're not gonna find her.

352
00:25:44,961 --> 00:25:46,587
Not unless she wants us to.

353
00:25:47,171 --> 00:25:49,173
All right. Let's go.

354
00:25:59,809 --> 00:26:01,703
Cody, a couple more minutes
and we're out of here.

355
00:26:01,727 --> 00:26:03,479
It's all good.

356
00:26:09,777 --> 00:26:12,196
Let's clarify the crazy
coming out of your mouth.

357
00:26:12,280 --> 00:26:13,906
You want us to jack a drug cartel?

358
00:26:14,240 --> 00:26:16,158
No. A trap house owned by a cartel.

359
00:26:16,242 --> 00:26:17,702
I was just at one of these places.

360
00:26:17,785 --> 00:26:19,787
I'm telling you, it's amateur hour.

361
00:26:19,870 --> 00:26:22,456
One lookout, one dealer,
bottom of the barrel dumb asses.

362
00:26:22,540 --> 00:26:25,001
A couple of junkies sleeping
in the corner. That's it.

363
00:26:25,084 --> 00:26:26,961
Maybe with the money
that we steal from him,

364
00:26:27,044 --> 00:26:28,713
Jesse and his mom can buy a house,

365
00:26:28,796 --> 00:26:31,132
- pay off her medical bill.
- Jesse can go to college.

366
00:26:31,215 --> 00:26:32,800
I just want to know what my job is.

367
00:26:32,883 --> 00:26:34,927
Kyle, you would have
a really important job.

368
00:26:35,011 --> 00:26:36,637
- Lay it on me.
- The lookout.

369
00:26:36,721 --> 00:26:38,973
Okay, I'm the lookout.

370
00:26:39,056 --> 00:26:42,059
Are we doing this for real
or are we just bullshitting?

371
00:26:42,143 --> 00:26:44,270
Deni, I don't love how quiet you're being.

372
00:26:44,603 --> 00:26:47,148
I'm thinking about it.

373
00:26:47,231 --> 00:26:48,899
Between us, we got it all covered.

374
00:26:48,983 --> 00:26:50,651
I'd be the getaway driver.

375
00:26:50,735 --> 00:26:53,529
And Deni, your mom takes you
to training exercises.

376
00:26:53,612 --> 00:26:55,364
So you know the basics.

377
00:26:55,448 --> 00:26:58,242
Even better, you know
where all the DEA off sites are.

378
00:26:58,326 --> 00:27:00,202
- So...
- You borrow your mum's keys

379
00:27:00,286 --> 00:27:01,829
and then boom, we have access

380
00:27:01,912 --> 00:27:03,497
to top of the line DEA equipment.

381
00:27:03,581 --> 00:27:06,459
All compliance gear only,
non-lethal, no one gets hurt.

382
00:27:06,542 --> 00:27:09,337
Look, even if we could rob
a trap house, then what?

383
00:27:09,420 --> 00:27:12,173
We can't just FedEx Jesse
a box full of drug money.

384
00:27:12,256 --> 00:27:13,966
You have to set up
offshore shell companies

385
00:27:14,050 --> 00:27:15,343
with a pristine laptop

386
00:27:15,426 --> 00:27:18,387
and open a ton of bank accounts,
but only with small deposits

387
00:27:18,471 --> 00:27:21,140
to make sure you stay under
the IRS reporting requirements.

388
00:27:21,223 --> 00:27:23,142
Your dad worked money laundering, right?

389
00:27:23,225 --> 00:27:25,227
- Ah, shit.
- So we're covered.

390
00:27:25,311 --> 00:27:27,521
Is this gonna be like
the outdoor survival club

391
00:27:27,605 --> 00:27:28,981
you tried to start?

392
00:27:29,065 --> 00:27:31,567
I'm being serious. These
assholes killed Jesse's dad.

393
00:27:31,650 --> 00:27:33,569
If one of our parents got killed

394
00:27:33,652 --> 00:27:35,738
and we asked Jesse
to help us out, he'd say yes.

395
00:27:35,821 --> 00:27:37,239
You know he would.

396
00:27:37,323 --> 00:27:38,991
I'm not saying let's do it,

397
00:27:39,075 --> 00:27:41,702
but it does sound pretty righteous.

398
00:27:41,786 --> 00:27:44,121
Doing this would be a huge risk, for sure.

399
00:27:44,205 --> 00:27:46,457
We've all been saying that
we want to help Jesse, right?

400
00:27:46,540 --> 00:27:49,210
So this is how.

401
00:27:49,293 --> 00:27:52,463
The DEA should be taking care
of them and they're not.

402
00:27:53,756 --> 00:27:59,220
So we will. We can do this,
but it has to be all of us.

403
00:28:23,994 --> 00:28:25,579
He's clear.

404
00:28:38,008 --> 00:28:40,344
Hi. I'm here for the order.

405
00:28:41,011 --> 00:28:45,141
You're all set. So walk away,
enjoy your new life.

406
00:28:46,559 --> 00:28:47,810
Thank you.

407
00:28:50,187 --> 00:28:51,981
A vehicle on the shoulder.

408
00:28:55,401 --> 00:28:57,111
Gun!

409
00:28:58,320 --> 00:29:00,739
Everyone on the floor.
Down on the floor, flat!

410
00:29:01,282 --> 00:29:02,616
Shit!

411
00:29:08,456 --> 00:29:09,790
Hit the pedal!

412
00:29:16,130 --> 00:29:18,632
Get down! Get down!!

413
00:29:21,177 --> 00:29:23,971
Ray! Ray, Ray, Ray, come on. That's it.

414
00:29:24,054 --> 00:29:25,639
Get down.

415
00:29:42,990 --> 00:29:46,911
Hey, look at you,
buddy. You're a lucky man.

416
00:29:46,994 --> 00:29:48,871
You're lucky, <i>hombre.</i>

417
00:29:48,954 --> 00:29:50,873
Looks pretty good on you.

418
00:29:54,001 --> 00:29:56,962
Natalia Cabrera, tell us about her.

419
00:30:00,633 --> 00:30:04,929
Okay, we get it. A lot of people
don't like talking to us.

420
00:30:05,012 --> 00:30:07,014
They've got families they want to protect.

421
00:30:07,097 --> 00:30:09,975
You don't have any family.

422
00:30:10,059 --> 00:30:12,186
You were recruited out of the orphanage.

423
00:30:12,269 --> 00:30:14,063
You got options.

424
00:30:15,564 --> 00:30:18,442
You killed a DEA agent in Texas.

425
00:30:19,276 --> 00:30:21,111
Even if we can't make that stick,

426
00:30:21,195 --> 00:30:22,905
we got you on the informant.

427
00:30:22,988 --> 00:30:24,990
People are gonna be lining up
to get on the jury

428
00:30:25,074 --> 00:30:26,867
to put you in the chair.

429
00:30:26,951 --> 00:30:29,662
The only way you survive this
is by talking to us.

430
00:30:31,288 --> 00:30:34,208
Natalia Cabrera. We know she's in El Paso.

431
00:30:34,291 --> 00:30:35,668
What's she doing here?

432
00:30:38,420 --> 00:30:44,134
Well, shit, I'll tell you,
<i>cerdos, </i>free of charge.

433
00:30:45,511 --> 00:30:48,889
Natalia Cabrera is in El Paso for you.

434
00:30:50,015 --> 00:30:51,850
She's here to crack the cover identities

435
00:30:51,934 --> 00:30:53,352
of all you DEA agents.

436
00:30:54,603 --> 00:30:58,983
She's digging.
She's spreading money around.

437
00:30:59,066 --> 00:31:02,987
They're gonna find you and wipe you out

438
00:31:03,070 --> 00:31:04,780
and all of your families.

439
00:31:23,299 --> 00:31:25,175
- Hey, Dad.
- Hey, kid.

440
00:31:25,259 --> 00:31:27,303
Look, something came up.
I'm gonna be at work late.

441
00:31:27,386 --> 00:31:30,180
- Okay, cool. Good to know.
- Did you have a good day?

442
00:31:30,264 --> 00:31:33,058
<i>Ah, it's been fine. Nothing special.</i>

443
00:31:34,184 --> 00:31:35,728
<i>- Don't stay out too late.</i>
- Okay.

444
00:31:35,811 --> 00:31:38,147
- We still need to be careful.
<i>- Okay, cool.</i>

445
00:31:38,230 --> 00:31:40,232
- Bye.
- See ya. Bye.

446
00:31:50,451 --> 00:31:53,162
Jesus,
he's gotta take a leak sometime.

447
00:31:53,245 --> 00:31:55,289
Why'd you say that?
Now I have to take a leak.

448
00:31:55,372 --> 00:31:56,790
- Me too.
- Me three.

449
00:31:56,874 --> 00:31:58,314
You all got bladder problems.

450
00:31:58,375 --> 00:32:00,002
How long do you guys want to wait?

451
00:32:00,085 --> 00:32:01,670
I have an essay due first period.

452
00:32:01,754 --> 00:32:03,922
You should do your homework
early on crime night.

453
00:32:04,006 --> 00:32:07,301
- Not getting cold feet, Yvonne?
- Absolutely.

454
00:32:08,260 --> 00:32:11,138
Again, this will fire a cartridge.

455
00:32:11,221 --> 00:32:14,475
If you miss,
this end still works as a taser.

456
00:32:14,558 --> 00:32:16,935
- I got it, I got it.
- What is your job?

457
00:32:17,019 --> 00:32:18,187
I sit in the car like a loser

458
00:32:18,270 --> 00:32:20,230
while you guys do all the cool shit.

459
00:32:20,314 --> 00:32:22,316
If things get messed up, I call 911.

460
00:32:22,399 --> 00:32:25,152
I don't wanna go to jail
'cause you lost your shit.

461
00:32:25,235 --> 00:32:28,322
I don't lose my shit. I'm ice cold.

462
00:32:28,405 --> 00:32:29,966
We can't go to jail. We're still minors.

463
00:32:29,990 --> 00:32:31,700
Yeah, but I'm not.

464
00:32:31,784 --> 00:32:35,454
Worst case, us three will do
a little time in juvey.

465
00:32:35,537 --> 00:32:37,164
When we turn 18, it all goes away.

466
00:32:37,247 --> 00:32:39,416
Cody will take the fall. It was his idea.

467
00:32:39,500 --> 00:32:40,668
Thanks.

468
00:32:40,751 --> 00:32:44,088
Guys, we don't have guns
but they probably definitely do.

469
00:32:45,255 --> 00:32:47,758
Maybe I should wear a flak jacket too?

470
00:32:51,679 --> 00:32:54,264
Hey, we're on. We're doing this?

471
00:32:56,183 --> 00:32:58,268
- Shit.
- Yes.

472
00:32:58,352 --> 00:32:59,603
- Yes.
- Shit.

473
00:33:00,396 --> 00:33:02,523
- Have fun without me.
- You want to trade?

474
00:33:02,606 --> 00:33:04,108
- No, bye. Get out.
- You want go?

475
00:33:04,191 --> 00:33:05,693
Okay.

476
00:33:10,989 --> 00:33:13,158
- For Jesse.
- Yeah, for Jesse.

477
00:33:24,211 --> 00:33:27,005
Okay, same plan. Zerg rush,
knock over the candle,

478
00:33:27,089 --> 00:33:28,966
take the cash, out.

479
00:34:18,015 --> 00:34:20,476
- What do we do?
- Don't know.

480
00:34:22,269 --> 00:34:24,563
That way. Go.

481
00:34:39,661 --> 00:34:40,954
Shit.

482
00:34:48,128 --> 00:34:49,713
Oh, shit.

483
00:34:51,423 --> 00:34:52,925
Oh, Jesus.

484
00:34:56,970 --> 00:34:58,680
I can't see! I can't see!

485
00:34:58,764 --> 00:35:00,974
- Okay. Get the money!
- Let's go.

486
00:35:01,058 --> 00:35:02,392
What's going on?

487
00:35:02,476 --> 00:35:04,394
Come on, come on, come on, come on.

488
00:35:05,270 --> 00:35:07,773
It's Cabrera's money!
You're making a big mistake!

489
00:35:09,858 --> 00:35:11,235
- Go!
- Follow me.

490
00:35:17,866 --> 00:35:19,326
Oh, shit.

491
00:35:23,163 --> 00:35:24,581
Shit!

492
00:35:32,756 --> 00:35:34,508
Cody, clear!

493
00:35:40,639 --> 00:35:42,474
- It's us!
- I knew you'd be okay.

494
00:35:42,558 --> 00:35:44,393
- I didn't call the cops!
- Good job!

495
00:35:44,476 --> 00:35:46,603
- Oh my God, that was insane!
- Shit.

496
00:35:46,937 --> 00:35:48,814
You guys okay? Let's go!

497
00:36:03,412 --> 00:36:05,539
- How are the eyes?
- Better. Coming back.

498
00:36:05,622 --> 00:36:08,000
We have a grand total. Wanna hear it?

499
00:36:08,083 --> 00:36:12,254
- Yeah.
- All in, we have $497.

500
00:36:12,337 --> 00:36:14,006
- Huh...
- Mm-hm.

501
00:36:16,008 --> 00:36:17,926
Oh my God.

502
00:36:18,010 --> 00:36:21,013
I don't think we're sending
Jesse to Yale with that.

503
00:36:21,096 --> 00:36:23,056
We're the biggest morons on the planet.

504
00:36:23,140 --> 00:36:25,893
We almost got ourselves killed
for not even 500 bucks.

505
00:36:25,976 --> 00:36:28,270
Our obituaries would be so sad.

506
00:36:28,353 --> 00:36:31,732
"Local teens executed. Should
have got an after-school job."

507
00:36:33,901 --> 00:36:35,903
- You know what? I'm proud of us.
- Really?

508
00:36:35,986 --> 00:36:37,070
- For real.
- Yeah?

509
00:36:37,154 --> 00:36:39,281
We did the thing
and when it all went to shit,

510
00:36:39,364 --> 00:36:41,116
nobody panicked, we stuck together

511
00:36:41,199 --> 00:36:42,534
and helped each other out.

512
00:36:42,618 --> 00:36:45,037
- That was a goddamn rush.
- Hell, yeah.

513
00:36:47,664 --> 00:36:51,418
Calm down.
There's no reason to panic.

514
00:36:53,670 --> 00:36:58,759
Vasquez will keep his mouth
shut. He'll do time. Besides...

515
00:36:59,593 --> 00:37:01,219
It was just a trap house.

516
00:37:01,303 --> 00:37:02,930
There was barely any money.

517
00:37:03,013 --> 00:37:04,490
It's not about the money.

518
00:37:04,514 --> 00:37:05,783
This makes us look weak!

519
00:37:05,807 --> 00:37:08,310
<i>First the tunnel, then this!</i>

520
00:37:08,393 --> 00:37:10,103
Open season on us.

521
00:37:10,187 --> 00:37:12,230
We cannot flinch.

522
00:37:12,314 --> 00:37:15,692
This happened
in your city, didn't it?

523
00:37:15,776 --> 00:37:18,820
Find out who it was
and make an example out of 'em?

524
00:37:21,198 --> 00:37:24,451
The squatter said the trap house
got knocked over last night.

525
00:37:24,534 --> 00:37:27,955
That was just a smash and grab.
These bodies happened later.

526
00:37:29,623 --> 00:37:32,125
Yeah, Benito's not
the forgiving type.

527
00:37:32,709 --> 00:37:34,711
We found a helmet with night vision.

528
00:37:35,545 --> 00:37:38,006
<i>These bastards aren't civilians.</i>

529
00:37:38,090 --> 00:37:40,342
Military grade. Very strange.

530
00:37:40,425 --> 00:37:43,720
No, it's not
strange. It was the DEA.

531
00:37:43,804 --> 00:37:45,347
They're going rogue.

532
00:37:45,430 --> 00:37:47,349
They lost their informant, their friend,

533
00:37:47,432 --> 00:37:50,852
and they're out for revenge, that's it.

534
00:37:50,936 --> 00:37:53,146
Who'd be dumb enough
to steal from them anyway?

535
00:37:53,230 --> 00:37:54,898
I doubt they know who it belonged to.

536
00:37:54,982 --> 00:37:58,610
- Was probably just a one-off.
- I hope so. For their sake.

537
00:38:04,992 --> 00:38:07,619
- Ow! My tongue.
- Let me get that.

538
00:38:07,703 --> 00:38:10,580
Oh! No, it's fine. I got it.

539
00:38:11,790 --> 00:38:14,001
To be honest, I'm a little nervous.

540
00:38:14,084 --> 00:38:16,420
Oh, I... I was nervous
because I thought you weren't.

541
00:38:16,503 --> 00:38:18,296
- So...
- Oh, yeah.

542
00:38:19,548 --> 00:38:20,674
Um...

543
00:38:21,883 --> 00:38:24,386
Sorry, this crazy woman's my mom.

544
00:38:24,469 --> 00:38:26,805
Oh no, I... trust me, I get that.

545
00:38:26,888 --> 00:38:29,850
- Yeah, your mom too?
- Uh, no, my dad.

546
00:38:30,517 --> 00:38:32,310
My mom passed away actually, so...

547
00:38:33,353 --> 00:38:35,897
- God, I'm sorry.
- Oh, no, no. I appreciate it.

548
00:38:35,981 --> 00:38:38,942
It was three years ago. Leukaemia, so...

549
00:38:40,110 --> 00:38:42,529
What about you and your folks?
Still together or...?

550
00:38:42,612 --> 00:38:44,990
Divorced. Dad's somewhere.

551
00:38:45,073 --> 00:38:48,118
He had a kid and decided,
it's not really my thing.

552
00:38:49,619 --> 00:38:52,664
Ask me, an overprotective father
kind of sounds nice.

553
00:38:53,707 --> 00:38:55,917
So, what's his deal?

554
00:38:56,001 --> 00:38:58,378
He's always been about his job.

555
00:38:58,462 --> 00:39:00,547
He's in construction, project manager.

556
00:39:00,630 --> 00:39:03,091
But now that it's just him,
he's gotta be the parent.

557
00:39:03,175 --> 00:39:06,303
Like, who's gonna keep me alive anyway.

558
00:39:06,386 --> 00:39:08,430
Sorry? Keep you alive?!

559
00:39:08,513 --> 00:39:09,574
What are you doing on the weekends?

560
00:39:09,598 --> 00:39:12,601
Like he owes that to my mom.

561
00:39:12,684 --> 00:39:14,519
It's just another job he's gotta do.

562
00:39:14,603 --> 00:39:17,481
Sounds like we have awesome families.

563
00:39:17,564 --> 00:39:19,524
Maybe that's why we're good lab partners.

564
00:39:19,983 --> 00:39:21,860
I'm gonna give myself a mission.

565
00:39:22,486 --> 00:39:25,030
I'm gonna make you happy you moved here.

566
00:39:25,113 --> 00:39:26,907
I'm gonna make you love El Paso.

567
00:39:26,990 --> 00:39:29,159
- Yeah.
- Boy likes a challenge.

568
00:39:45,133 --> 00:39:47,302
<i>Yeah, no, we're just...
We're getting settled in.</i>

569
00:39:47,385 --> 00:39:50,347
<i>- How is your mom doing, Jesse?
- Uh, she's all right.</i>

570
00:39:50,430 --> 00:39:52,432
<i>Um, she's just, you know, job hunting,</i>

571
00:39:52,516 --> 00:39:54,142
<i>which has been kind of difficult...</i>

572
00:39:55,227 --> 00:39:58,688
<i>Jesus! All right, would you
piss ants please shut up.</i>

573
00:39:58,772 --> 00:40:01,608
<i>Hey, I'm on the phone! Stop it!</i>

574
00:40:01,691 --> 00:40:03,836
<i>I'm gonna step outside
and deal with that.</i>

575
00:40:03,860 --> 00:40:05,779
<i>- Can I call you guys back?
- Yeah, of course!</i>

576
00:40:05,862 --> 00:40:06,905
<i>Thank you!</i>

577
00:40:07,823 --> 00:40:09,366
I'm never having kids.

578
00:40:09,449 --> 00:40:11,243
Poor Jesse.

579
00:40:22,671 --> 00:40:25,298
We didn't get what
we need from the trap house.

580
00:40:25,382 --> 00:40:27,151
That's fine. Rookie mistake.
Won't happen again.

581
00:40:27,175 --> 00:40:29,636
Right, because we're not robbing
any more trap houses.

582
00:40:29,719 --> 00:40:32,305
Next we're gonna be hitting
one of Cabrera's money mules.

583
00:40:32,389 --> 00:40:34,558
- So what now?
- The mule that collects cash

584
00:40:34,641 --> 00:40:36,643
from the dealers. Spreads it
around cash businesses

585
00:40:36,726 --> 00:40:38,204
controlled by the cartels to clean it.

586
00:40:38,228 --> 00:40:39,228
- I love it.
- Yeah.

587
00:40:39,271 --> 00:40:41,064
- Cody!
- I'm serious.

588
00:40:41,148 --> 00:40:45,235
This is our mule. They call him
El Viejo Malhumorado.

589
00:40:45,318 --> 00:40:47,821
- Grumpy old man.
- He looks like a hobo.

590
00:40:47,904 --> 00:40:49,865
- Hm.
- He's kind of hot.

591
00:40:49,948 --> 00:40:51,783
The idea is to keep a low profile.

592
00:40:51,867 --> 00:40:54,286
Every week he does
the same circuit around El Paso.

593
00:40:54,369 --> 00:40:56,121
Laundromats, pawn shops, bars.

594
00:40:56,204 --> 00:40:58,248
His van has to be filled with cash.

595
00:40:58,331 --> 00:41:02,210
- What's filled?
- Half a million. At least.

596
00:41:02,294 --> 00:41:04,796
That's Jesse and his mom
well taken care of.

597
00:41:04,880 --> 00:41:07,257
So, what do we think?

598
00:41:11,428 --> 00:41:12,554
- I'm in...
- Yes.

599
00:41:12,637 --> 00:41:16,349
If we don't pull
the entire thing out of our ass.

600
00:41:16,433 --> 00:41:18,852
This time we actually have a plan.

601
00:41:18,935 --> 00:41:20,812
El Viejo does
the same route every week?

602
00:41:20,896 --> 00:41:22,647
- Yep.
- Great.

603
00:41:22,731 --> 00:41:25,192
Then we have time
to really think this through.

604
00:41:25,275 --> 00:41:27,861
If we do it smart this time,
then I'm in too.

605
00:41:27,944 --> 00:41:30,989
- Then smart it is.
- Letting y'all know I'm also in.

606
00:41:31,072 --> 00:41:32,115
Obviously.

607
00:41:33,950 --> 00:41:35,535
So, where do we start?

608
00:41:35,619 --> 00:41:38,538
I know where our parents
would start. Recon.

609
00:41:38,622 --> 00:41:40,248
A shit ton of recon.

610
00:41:46,963 --> 00:41:49,174
El Viejo is always
followed by two armed guards

611
00:41:49,257 --> 00:41:51,009
in a sedan.

612
00:41:51,092 --> 00:41:53,386
No way we just walk up
and taser those guys.

613
00:41:53,470 --> 00:41:56,681
You're right. For them
we need some heavy artillery.

614
00:41:56,765 --> 00:41:59,226
- Beanbag shotguns.
- They're non-lethal.

615
00:41:59,309 --> 00:42:01,029
They just knock you
down for a while.

616
00:42:01,061 --> 00:42:03,813
Beanbag shotguns.
I could handle one of those.

617
00:42:03,897 --> 00:42:06,650
Kyle, I don't know. Deni and I
grew up hunting. You didn't.

618
00:42:06,733 --> 00:42:10,320
I always beat your ass
at Fortnite. So I'm the master.

619
00:42:10,987 --> 00:42:13,990
If they're up on it, why doesn't
the DEA just shut him down?

620
00:42:14,074 --> 00:42:15,909
He's not the prize for them.

621
00:42:15,992 --> 00:42:17,494
They're just gathering intel for now.

622
00:42:17,577 --> 00:42:20,038
They put a GPS
on his van, see where he goes,

623
00:42:20,121 --> 00:42:22,332
- who he talks to.
- So we do the same.

624
00:42:22,415 --> 00:42:24,709
We'll make sure
our parents aren't following.

625
00:42:26,253 --> 00:42:29,506
<i>♪ ...an evacuation zone and
I think I need to operate now ♪</i>

626
00:42:29,589 --> 00:42:32,259
<i>♪ And if all goes well
I'll return to the world...</i>

627
00:42:36,763 --> 00:42:37,931
This is where we do it.

628
00:42:38,014 --> 00:42:39,432
The neighbourhood should be empty

629
00:42:39,516 --> 00:42:40,976
so there should be no traffic.

630
00:42:41,059 --> 00:42:42,703
It'll be easy
to get in and out of there fast.

631
00:42:42,727 --> 00:42:44,354
What about the customers?

632
00:42:44,437 --> 00:42:47,440
We don't want anyone
to see what's happening.

633
00:42:47,524 --> 00:42:50,193
- Kyle, that's your job.
- Kyle gets a job?

634
00:42:50,277 --> 00:42:53,071
- I'm a part of this!
- Yeah, he's a part of this.

635
00:42:58,994 --> 00:43:01,037
On the day, let's leave
our phones at school.

636
00:43:01,121 --> 00:43:02,914
Keep our location history clean.

637
00:43:02,998 --> 00:43:05,375
When we get El Viejo's van,
where the hell do we put it?

638
00:43:05,458 --> 00:43:07,168
My grandpa's place. It's out of town.

639
00:43:07,252 --> 00:43:09,713
There's an old barn. It's perfect.

640
00:43:54,716 --> 00:43:56,343
Let's go!

641
00:44:22,744 --> 00:44:25,497
- Let her go!
- I said drop it!

642
00:44:25,580 --> 00:44:27,165
Okay.

643
00:44:29,959 --> 00:44:32,379
Shit. No, no, no.

644
00:44:32,462 --> 00:44:34,130
Come on, come on, come on.

645
00:44:56,111 --> 00:44:57,862
Shit.

646
00:44:57,946 --> 00:44:59,697
I got the keys!

647
00:44:59,781 --> 00:45:01,908
I got her! Take this.

648
00:45:05,745 --> 00:45:08,498
- Come on. Let's go.
- Let's get out of here!

649
00:45:11,918 --> 00:45:14,212
- Fuck you!
- Yoo-hoo.

650
00:45:16,339 --> 00:45:20,009
Suck on my bag, biatch!
Fortnite, I told you!

651
00:45:20,093 --> 00:45:21,928
Yeah, nice one!

652
00:45:26,141 --> 00:45:28,184
Come on, let's go. Go, go, go, go!

653
00:45:29,686 --> 00:45:31,146
Oh, good job, Kyle.

654
00:45:39,904 --> 00:45:43,324
Holy shit! Did you see
that? Is your head okay, Deni?

655
00:45:43,408 --> 00:45:45,243
Yeah. Are you okay?

656
00:45:45,326 --> 00:45:47,537
Yeah, he's much better looking in person.

657
00:45:52,208 --> 00:45:53,751
- Bingo!
- Whoa!

658
00:45:53,835 --> 00:45:56,087
He's still on us! This isn't over yet!

659
00:46:06,097 --> 00:46:08,099
If this ends in a police chase,
we're screwed,

660
00:46:08,183 --> 00:46:10,018
so keep your masks on!

661
00:46:16,691 --> 00:46:18,526
Doors!

662
00:46:20,612 --> 00:46:24,532
Move, I got this. I got you all back!

663
00:46:25,116 --> 00:46:29,245
- Shit! Sorry!
- It's okay! Doors open!

664
00:46:29,329 --> 00:46:30,455
Now!

665
00:46:40,173 --> 00:46:43,843
I've got you, you old son of a bitch.

666
00:46:43,927 --> 00:46:46,429
Woo!

667
00:46:46,513 --> 00:46:47,722
Fortnite!

668
00:46:47,805 --> 00:46:48,973
Woo!

669
00:46:49,557 --> 00:46:52,936
Oh my God! That was insane.

670
00:46:55,063 --> 00:46:58,358
- Wow, did you see that?
- Wait. Get a selfie.

671
00:47:03,196 --> 00:47:04,781
<i>♪ That's right! ♪</i>

672
00:47:09,577 --> 00:47:11,871
<i>♪ I got a little funny doggy ♪</i>

673
00:47:11,955 --> 00:47:13,915
<i>♪ Set your name straight right off ♪</i>

674
00:47:13,998 --> 00:47:17,377
<i>♪ Oooooo ♪</i>

675
00:47:17,794 --> 00:47:18,795
<i>♪ Woohoo ♪</i>

676
00:47:18,878 --> 00:47:21,214
<i>♪ I know a disco kitten named Minnie ♪</i>

677
00:47:21,297 --> 00:47:25,009
<i>♪ She'll put a new smile
on your necktie, that's right...</i>

678
00:47:27,971 --> 00:47:31,015
Yeah, I gotta go.
Hey, hey El Viejo. We got him.

679
00:47:31,099 --> 00:47:33,309
Yeah? Please tell me
his head's still attached.

680
00:47:33,393 --> 00:47:34,561
We caught a break this time.

681
00:47:34,644 --> 00:47:36,271
He just walked into a field office.

682
00:47:36,354 --> 00:47:37,522
Smart man.

683
00:47:37,605 --> 00:47:39,667
He knows Benito's gonna kill him
for losing that shipment.

684
00:47:39,691 --> 00:47:41,693
- He want witness protection?
- What do you think?

685
00:47:41,776 --> 00:47:43,152
I'll see what he's got.

686
00:47:43,236 --> 00:47:46,447
- So it was a crew?
- Yes, there were four of them.

687
00:47:46,531 --> 00:47:49,367
- Two women and two men.
- You get a look at them?

688
00:47:49,450 --> 00:47:51,995
No, they used tear gas on us.

689
00:47:52,078 --> 00:47:54,789
They all had gas masks on. I couldn't see.

690
00:47:54,872 --> 00:47:57,208
- Cartel?
- Oh, God. No. God, no.

691
00:47:57,292 --> 00:47:59,460
I wouldn't be here if it was them.

692
00:47:59,544 --> 00:48:02,380
This was sloppy, not pros.

693
00:48:02,463 --> 00:48:06,467
You could tell there was...
They did get to jump on us.

694
00:48:06,551 --> 00:48:10,555
But the two guards with me,
I can tell you all about them.

695
00:48:10,638 --> 00:48:13,641
Oh, come on. Those guys
are long gone, you know that.

696
00:48:14,517 --> 00:48:16,477
Come on, give us something
that goes up the chain.

697
00:48:16,769 --> 00:48:18,438
I... I handled my end only...

698
00:48:18,521 --> 00:48:21,232
What do you know about Natalia Cabrera?

699
00:48:21,316 --> 00:48:24,360
- Well, I've heard the name.
- Any idea what she looks like?

700
00:48:26,446 --> 00:48:27,905
- No, I...
- Come on, brother.

701
00:48:27,989 --> 00:48:30,533
You want WITSEC, you're gonna
have to do better than that.

702
00:48:30,617 --> 00:48:34,787
I can't give you Benito
and his top guys, all right?

703
00:48:34,871 --> 00:48:38,124
I can tell you more about
how they move things around.

704
00:48:39,542 --> 00:48:43,713
I can tell you about the beer
truck. That's something.

705
00:48:44,380 --> 00:48:46,257
Who the hell is doing this?!

706
00:48:46,341 --> 00:48:48,343
How come you haven't found them? Tell me!

707
00:48:48,426 --> 00:48:50,261
Our whole network is burnt.

708
00:48:50,345 --> 00:48:53,348
<i>I have to start
everything from scratch.</i>

709
00:48:53,431 --> 00:48:54,891
I'll find them!

710
00:48:54,974 --> 00:48:57,644
It's the DEA pigs.

711
00:48:57,727 --> 00:49:00,188
They're making fun of us!

712
00:49:01,689 --> 00:49:06,903
I'm sure they're laughing at us.
I'm sure it's them!

713
00:49:06,986 --> 00:49:08,589
The DEA
doesn't operate that way.

714
00:49:08,613 --> 00:49:10,239
Oh yeah? Then what?!

715
00:49:10,323 --> 00:49:12,450
- Don't be paranoid.
- <i>I want...</i>

716
00:49:12,533 --> 00:49:15,828
I want the DEA names,
you have to prove it to me.

717
00:49:15,912 --> 00:49:18,790
<i>I want their names. I want their faces.</i>

718
00:49:18,873 --> 00:49:21,000
I want their addresses.
I want them dead...

719
00:49:21,084 --> 00:49:24,837
I want their wives
and kids dead. Their pets too!

720
00:49:24,921 --> 00:49:25,963
Set a trap!

721
00:49:29,801 --> 00:49:31,636
- Teresa.
- I've got to get to class.

722
00:49:31,719 --> 00:49:33,721
I'm sorry I haven't been around, for real.

723
00:49:33,805 --> 00:49:35,473
It's just wrestling has been insane.

724
00:49:35,556 --> 00:49:37,183
It's fine, I just don't need this.

725
00:49:37,266 --> 00:49:41,104
I want to make it up to you.
So how about go hiking with me.

726
00:49:41,437 --> 00:49:43,481
I know a great spot, it'll be epic.

727
00:49:44,899 --> 00:49:46,984
- I don't know.
- Look, if you don't go then...

728
00:49:47,068 --> 00:49:50,655
I'll be too devastated to study,
and then we'll both fail chem.

729
00:49:53,324 --> 00:49:55,618
- This is extortion.
- It's actually blackmail.

730
00:49:55,702 --> 00:49:57,120
Okay.

731
00:50:11,384 --> 00:50:13,261
- Wow!
- Yeah, I know.

732
00:50:14,470 --> 00:50:18,558
My mom used to take me here.
She loved the mountains.

733
00:50:18,641 --> 00:50:20,393
What was she like?

734
00:50:20,476 --> 00:50:22,478
She was really gentle.

735
00:50:22,562 --> 00:50:24,731
She'd always joke

736
00:50:24,814 --> 00:50:26,333
that she couldn't wait
to become a little old lady.

737
00:50:26,357 --> 00:50:28,609
She still had
the whole mama bear thing going,

738
00:50:28,693 --> 00:50:30,361
so you wouldn't want to mess with her.

739
00:50:30,445 --> 00:50:33,906
Was it a good marriage?
Were they at least happy?

740
00:50:33,990 --> 00:50:38,453
Yeah, they were.
I couldn't tell you how though,

741
00:50:38,536 --> 00:50:43,958
because my dad is so massively
closed off and she was so there.

742
