978
01:06:19,601 --> 01:06:20,894
Let's go.

979
01:06:36,326 --> 01:06:37,828
<i>In position.</i>

980
01:06:38,495 --> 01:06:40,330
<i>In position.</i>

981
01:06:44,710 --> 01:06:46,545
In position.

982
01:06:52,676 --> 01:06:54,886
Keep your eyes on the beer truck.

983
01:06:54,970 --> 01:06:57,305
<i>It looks like they got an escort.</i>

984
01:06:57,389 --> 01:06:59,391
Copy that. See the beer truck.

985
01:06:59,474 --> 01:07:01,560
One follow vehicle, three inside.

986
01:07:15,240 --> 01:07:16,491
Let's go!

987
01:07:23,749 --> 01:07:25,417
- All right.
- Ready? Let's do this.

988
01:07:25,500 --> 01:07:26,710
Okay.

989
01:07:29,546 --> 01:07:31,590
All right. Now!

990
01:07:35,635 --> 01:07:36,803
What the hell?

991
01:07:36,887 --> 01:07:39,139
- Ray, what are we doing?
- Wash, hold your position.

992
01:07:39,222 --> 01:07:40,862
Albright, Matthews, let's take 'em there.

993
01:07:40,932 --> 01:07:42,058
Copy that. Let's go.

994
01:07:42,142 --> 01:07:43,786
<i>Don't let them
get back out on the road.</i>

995
01:07:43,810 --> 01:07:45,187
Let's go!

996
01:07:58,742 --> 01:08:01,536
Shit! No keys! No keys! No keys!

997
01:08:01,620 --> 01:08:04,414
- Crap!
- Check his pockets!

998
01:08:05,415 --> 01:08:07,459
Here they are!

999
01:08:10,921 --> 01:08:13,590
DEA, everyone on the ground!

1000
01:08:13,673 --> 01:08:15,300
DEA, get down.

1001
01:08:18,804 --> 01:08:21,556
- Oh, shit!
- Kyle, let's move.

1002
01:08:22,849 --> 01:08:24,392
DEA!

1003
01:08:24,935 --> 01:08:26,770
Get down. Get down!

1004
01:08:26,853 --> 01:08:28,814
Shit, that's my mom!

1005
01:08:33,109 --> 01:08:35,654
DEA, on the ground!

1006
01:08:37,155 --> 01:08:38,740
Drop your weapon!

1007
01:08:50,418 --> 01:08:52,087
- Kyle, come on.
- Okay, okay.

1008
01:08:52,170 --> 01:08:53,839
Let's go, let's go!

1009
01:09:30,083 --> 01:09:32,127
<i>Wash,
beer truck heading your way.</i>

1010
01:09:33,879 --> 01:09:37,757
- I'm on it. I'll take it out.
- Stand down. Stand down.

1011
01:09:37,841 --> 01:09:39,843
I'm on it!

1012
01:09:41,177 --> 01:09:44,764
I just wanna go home. I'm sorry.
This isn't what I signed up for!

1013
01:09:44,848 --> 01:09:47,559
- We're good, we're good!
- No, we're not!

1014
01:09:47,642 --> 01:09:49,519
Oh shit. Oh shit. Oh shit.

1015
01:09:49,853 --> 01:09:51,688
I got this!

1016
01:09:55,525 --> 01:09:56,902
What the hell?!

1017
01:09:56,985 --> 01:09:58,528
Wash, stand down.

1018
01:10:00,655 --> 01:10:02,032
Cody, slow down!

1019
01:10:03,241 --> 01:10:05,911
Stand down! That's an order!

1020
01:10:17,047 --> 01:10:18,798
Goddammit!

1021
01:10:22,427 --> 01:10:25,680
- You okay?
- No! I'm not okay, Cody!

1022
01:10:25,764 --> 01:10:27,682
I'm sorry. Okay, I'm sorry.

1023
01:10:27,766 --> 01:10:29,851
I just wanna go home, bro'.
I wanna go home.

1024
01:11:00,465 --> 01:11:03,718
Hey... hey! What was that?
What's going on?

1025
01:11:03,802 --> 01:11:06,638
- Get a look at them?
- I could have followed them!

1026
01:11:08,723 --> 01:11:10,266
Ray, I know what's going on!

1027
01:11:12,268 --> 01:11:18,233
Padilla, wasn't your fault.
It wasn't mine, okay?

1028
01:11:18,316 --> 01:11:21,361
It happened.
And he'd want us to keep going.

1029
01:11:21,444 --> 01:11:25,073
He'd want to keep taking risks.
To do our jobs.

1030
01:11:26,282 --> 01:11:30,245
Yeah, I know. I know you're right. Thanks.

1031
01:11:43,258 --> 01:11:45,176
Oh my God.

1032
01:11:46,177 --> 01:11:47,637
What did you do?

1033
01:11:47,721 --> 01:11:50,348
I know. That got way out of hand.

1034
01:11:50,432 --> 01:11:52,392
- You think?
- Yvonne, our parents were there.

1035
01:11:52,475 --> 01:11:53,977
What? Are they okay?

1036
01:11:54,060 --> 01:11:55,895
Yeah, they're fine. That was a mess.

1037
01:12:02,318 --> 01:12:04,154
They're not cold.

1038
01:12:07,240 --> 01:12:09,242
- No way.
- Where's the cash?

1039
01:12:12,746 --> 01:12:14,247
Oh, God.

1040
01:12:14,330 --> 01:12:16,875
Cody, stop!
Stop! There's no cash!

1041
01:12:18,251 --> 01:12:19,794
This is worth, I don't know...

1042
01:12:19,878 --> 01:12:21,337
A million. Tens of millions!

1043
01:12:21,421 --> 01:12:24,090
The money we stole
from the cartel was nothing!

1044
01:12:24,174 --> 01:12:25,884
They're gonna be looking for it!

1045
01:12:25,967 --> 01:12:26,885
I know!

1046
01:12:26,968 --> 01:12:28,648
What if there's
a tracking beacon in there?

1047
01:12:28,678 --> 01:12:30,096
- There's not!
- How do you know?

1048
01:12:30,180 --> 01:12:32,807
Because we'd already be dead!

1049
01:12:45,612 --> 01:12:48,073
Yvonne told me. Goddamn it, Cody!

1050
01:12:48,156 --> 01:12:50,700
Everything's gonna be fine.
We're cleaning it up now.

1051
01:12:50,784 --> 01:12:52,869
We should have quit after El Viejo.

1052
01:12:52,952 --> 01:12:55,246
This is over, Cody. It has to be.

1053
01:12:55,789 --> 01:12:58,124
Yeah, it's definitely over.

1054
01:13:26,820 --> 01:13:30,156
Hey. So I sat down with everyone
who was read in on the Cabreras.

1055
01:13:30,240 --> 01:13:32,408
They all have alibis for all the heists.

1056
01:13:32,492 --> 01:13:34,744
- Yeah, good.
- Yep.

1057
01:13:34,828 --> 01:13:37,664
That doesn't mean they couldn't
have passed the intel on.

1058
01:13:37,747 --> 01:13:40,208
To friends or family, even.

1059
01:13:40,291 --> 01:13:43,044
Yeah, they could've.
A lot of possibilities.

1060
01:13:43,128 --> 01:13:44,546
Yeah.

1061
01:13:46,339 --> 01:13:51,469
Well, if we don't get 'em,
the cartel will, right?

1062
01:13:52,512 --> 01:13:54,389
And they don't forget.

1063
01:14:10,572 --> 01:14:12,323
Cody, come out here.

1064
01:14:12,407 --> 01:14:13,992
Jesus, I thought you forgot.

1065
01:14:15,952 --> 01:14:17,954
Oh, dammit.

1066
01:14:24,627 --> 01:14:26,421
- Hey.
- Hi.

1067
01:14:27,422 --> 01:14:29,048
Hi!

1068
01:14:29,132 --> 01:14:31,968
Hi, uh, please come in. You look great.

1069
01:14:32,051 --> 01:14:34,345
- Thanks.
- Yeah, Dad, Teresa. Teresa, Dad.

1070
01:14:34,429 --> 01:14:35,346
Hi.

1071
01:14:35,430 --> 01:14:36,615
Mr Seale, it's really nice to meet you.

1072
01:14:36,639 --> 01:14:38,784
- Yeah, likewise. Call me Ray.
- Ray, this is my mother.

1073
01:14:38,808 --> 01:14:40,018
- Hi Ray.
- How are you?

1074
01:14:40,101 --> 01:14:41,352
- Call me Lydia.
- Lydia...

1075
01:14:41,436 --> 01:14:43,855
- Cody, nice to finally meet you.
- Yeah.

1076
01:14:43,938 --> 01:14:45,690
Teresa talks about you all the time.

1077
01:14:45,773 --> 01:14:47,442
- Right?
- Mom...

1078
01:14:48,067 --> 01:14:50,361
All right... come on in.

1079
01:14:50,445 --> 01:14:52,488
See, I already embarrassed her.

1080
01:14:52,572 --> 01:14:55,200
Well, that's what parents are for, right?

1081
01:14:58,077 --> 01:14:59,829
We were mostly commercial,

1082
01:14:59,913 --> 01:15:01,623
but now we're focusing on residential.

1083
01:15:01,706 --> 01:15:03,791
It's like everyone's moving to Texas.

1084
01:15:03,875 --> 01:15:04,751
Yeah, exactly.

1085
01:15:04,834 --> 01:15:06,711
- That's where all the money is.
- You okay?

1086
01:15:06,794 --> 01:15:08,379
Yeah.

1087
01:15:09,047 --> 01:15:12,342
Um... excuse me,
uh, where's your restroom?

1088
01:15:13,301 --> 01:15:15,303
Down the hallway,
second door to the right.

1089
01:15:15,386 --> 01:15:17,138
Gotcha.

1090
01:15:21,601 --> 01:15:24,687
Did you cook? This is delicious.

1091
01:15:24,771 --> 01:15:26,898
Thank you.

1092
01:15:59,722 --> 01:16:01,408
- Oh man, seven hours.
- Seven hours.

1093
01:16:01,432 --> 01:16:03,786
- Yeah, about seven hours.
- Oh wow, that's a long time.

1094
01:16:03,810 --> 01:16:06,020
Yeah. Used to go up there
fishing all the time.

1095
01:16:10,441 --> 01:16:13,569
Being a single parent is tough, right?

1096
01:16:13,653 --> 01:16:15,321
How have you managed it?

1097
01:16:15,405 --> 01:16:18,074
I had to let go of the idea of perfect.

1098
01:16:18,157 --> 01:16:20,660
Perfect went out the door
along with her dad.

1099
01:16:20,743 --> 01:16:23,413
I've settled for the best I can.

1100
01:16:24,956 --> 01:16:28,001
Looks like you're doing
a great job with him.

1101
01:16:28,084 --> 01:16:31,379
Uh... Yeah, I mean, I hope so.

1102
01:16:31,462 --> 01:16:34,424
No one ever tells you if you're
being a bad parent, you know?

1103
01:16:34,507 --> 01:16:36,217
Yeah, figure it out on your own.

1104
01:16:36,301 --> 01:16:38,428
Cody's a good kid.

1105
01:16:39,554 --> 01:16:41,347
Got a great heart.

1106
01:16:41,431 --> 01:16:45,059
Just makes bad decisions sometimes.

1107
01:16:47,270 --> 01:16:49,981
Sorry, I'm not trying to scare
your daughter off or anything.

1108
01:16:50,064 --> 01:16:53,568
Don't worry. No chance of that.

1109
01:16:53,651 --> 01:16:54,986
Yeah.

1110
01:16:55,069 --> 01:16:58,865
Family's hard. Oh, trust me, I know.

1111
01:16:58,948 --> 01:17:00,158
Yeah.

1112
01:17:00,241 --> 01:17:02,952
What's the saying?
You choose your friends...

1113
01:17:03,036 --> 01:17:04,412
- But not your family.
- Yeah.

1114
01:17:04,495 --> 01:17:05,955
- Right, cheers to that.
<i>- Salud.</i>

1115
01:17:06,039 --> 01:17:07,707
- Thank you so much.
- Thanks for coming.

1116
01:17:07,790 --> 01:17:09,917
- Pleasure. Pleasure.
- Bye, Cody.

1117
01:17:21,429 --> 01:17:24,307
- Is everything okay?
- Let's get out of town tomorrow.

1118
01:17:24,390 --> 01:17:27,310
Go fishing. We haven't done
that in a long time.

1119
01:17:27,393 --> 01:17:29,854
Give us a chance to talk.

1120
01:17:31,939 --> 01:17:33,483
All right.

1121
01:17:35,818 --> 01:17:37,320
Good job.

1122
01:17:37,403 --> 01:17:39,530
They'll lead us
to the whole DEA team.

1123
01:17:43,743 --> 01:17:45,620
What?

1124
01:18:08,226 --> 01:18:10,436
Hey, what's up?

1125
01:18:10,520 --> 01:18:14,816
<i>Hey, Cody.
Thanks for dinner tonight.</i>

1126
01:18:15,691 --> 01:18:16,734
Teresa?!

1127
01:18:16,818 --> 01:18:18,653
<i>I did enjoy getting to know you.</i>

1128
01:18:18,736 --> 01:18:21,280
<i>You won't believe me after this,
but it's true.</i>

1129
01:18:21,364 --> 01:18:23,991
Now we want our beer truck back
with everything inside of it.

1130
01:18:25,618 --> 01:18:29,497
- Where's Deni?
- It's important you stay calm.

1131
01:18:29,580 --> 01:18:31,666
- It's important for Deni.
- Let me talk to her.

1132
01:18:31,749 --> 01:18:33,501
<i>Okay.</i>

1133
01:18:34,419 --> 01:18:36,587
Cody, don't come over here!

1134
01:18:38,005 --> 01:18:40,842
Okay, just... just tell me what you want.

1135
01:18:40,925 --> 01:18:42,969
I'm gonna send you a location.

1136
01:18:43,052 --> 01:18:45,638
Be here with our beer truck
within two hours or Deni dies.

1137
01:18:45,721 --> 01:18:49,434
<i>Daddy shows up, Deni dies too.
Are you clear?</i>

1138
01:18:49,517 --> 01:18:55,022
- Yes.
- Guess I'll see you soon.

1139
01:20:40,962 --> 01:20:43,047
Cody! Get down!

1140
01:20:57,186 --> 01:21:01,274
Wash, I'm under attack.
My cover's blown. Call everyone.

1141
01:21:22,295 --> 01:21:24,005
Shit.

1142
01:21:41,147 --> 01:21:43,274
Hey, everyone okay?

1143
01:21:43,357 --> 01:21:45,597
Albright and Reynolds are fine.
They're at the office now

1144
01:21:45,651 --> 01:21:47,653
- locking it down.
- Thank God.

1145
01:21:47,737 --> 01:21:50,656
<i>Listen, you said Cody was
visiting Deni at the hospital,</i>

1146
01:21:50,740 --> 01:21:52,617
I'm here now, and she's not in her room.

1147
01:21:52,700 --> 01:21:54,452
Matthews is freaking out.

1148
01:21:56,704 --> 01:22:01,042
Run a trace on Cody's phone.
Get his current location.

1149
01:22:01,125 --> 01:22:04,003
<i>And run ID checks
on Lydia and Teresa Flores.</i>

1150
01:22:04,086 --> 01:22:08,090
Okay. Listen, everything's
going to be fine. Okay?

1151
01:22:46,921 --> 01:22:51,550
Lydia Flores... EPPD just got
to her house. It's been torched.

1152
01:22:51,634 --> 01:22:54,178
No sign of her or the daughter.

1153
01:23:16,909 --> 01:23:18,244
Run silent.

1154
01:23:18,327 --> 01:23:20,454
Approach the extraction
with extreme caution.

1155
01:23:20,538 --> 01:23:22,373
Watch your crossfire
and watch your backdrop.

1156
01:23:41,559 --> 01:23:44,145
Don't shoot, I have a bomb
in here. Don't shoot!

1157
01:23:51,610 --> 01:23:55,281
Don't shoot, don't shoot! I have a bomb!

1158
01:23:55,364 --> 01:23:57,032
A bomb?

1159
01:23:57,116 --> 01:23:58,659
You are a mad scientist.

1160
01:24:09,712 --> 01:24:11,505
It could be real, he knows this stuff.

1161
01:24:11,589 --> 01:24:13,257
We were in chem class together.

1162
01:24:13,340 --> 01:24:15,718
Isn't that right, Cody?
Those were fun times.

1163
01:24:15,801 --> 01:24:17,636
Did you know the whole time?

1164
01:24:17,720 --> 01:24:20,723
We knew there were DEA kids at
school, but we didn't know who.

1165
01:24:20,806 --> 01:24:22,576
<i>I saw you hanging out.
Such a weird group of friends.</i>

1166
01:24:22,600 --> 01:24:24,518
<i>It made me curious.</i>

1167
01:24:24,852 --> 01:24:25,954
<i>Then after the tunnel raid, we wondered</i>

1168
01:24:25,978 --> 01:24:28,272
<i>if we'd made an orphan,</i>

1169
01:24:28,355 --> 01:24:30,316
<i>but I wasn't sure
until after you and I hooked up.</i>

1170
01:24:34,945 --> 01:24:36,864
Good for you.

1171
01:24:37,615 --> 01:24:38,908
You win.

1172
01:24:38,991 --> 01:24:40,910
Now just let Deni go.

1173
01:24:48,709 --> 01:24:50,419
Look, very good!

1174
01:24:50,503 --> 01:24:51,754
Truck looks nice.

1175
01:24:51,837 --> 01:24:54,298
But why are they still alive?

1176
01:24:54,381 --> 01:24:56,842
- I'm gonna light this up!
- No, you're not.

1177
01:24:56,926 --> 01:24:58,552
That's not a bomb.

1178
01:24:58,636 --> 01:25:00,471
- Look at him, he's all talk!
- Watch me!

1179
01:25:00,554 --> 01:25:02,807
- We are!
- Kill this mother...

1180
01:25:12,983 --> 01:25:14,401
Shit.

1181
01:25:14,485 --> 01:25:16,445
Kill him. Kill him!

1182
01:25:18,614 --> 01:25:20,491
Kill that bastard!

1183
01:25:32,002 --> 01:25:34,088
Motherfuckers!

1184
01:25:39,009 --> 01:25:40,427
Damn.

1185
01:25:53,440 --> 01:25:55,359
Over here!

1186
01:26:03,951 --> 01:26:05,619
Let's go!

1187
01:26:09,748 --> 01:26:11,667
Get down. Get down!

1188
01:26:21,302 --> 01:26:22,595
Go, go, go!

1189
01:26:22,678 --> 01:26:24,555
Let's take her. We'll trade her.

1190
01:26:24,638 --> 01:26:26,348
Go with your sister.

1191
01:26:28,934 --> 01:26:30,728
- Benito!
- I'll meet you later.

1192
01:26:30,811 --> 01:26:33,272
- Look after your sister!
- Hurry up!

1193
01:26:33,355 --> 01:26:34,815
Go!

1194
01:26:49,997 --> 01:26:51,832
Goddamnit, Cody!

1195
01:26:52,708 --> 01:26:54,418
Hey!

1196
01:27:00,257 --> 01:27:02,468
- Shit!
- Goddamn it, Ray!

1197
01:27:06,013 --> 01:27:07,056
Ray!

1198
01:27:12,853 --> 01:27:14,939
- And Benito?
- He's dead.

1199
01:27:25,240 --> 01:27:27,868
Stop! I'm sick of you, brat!

1200
01:27:27,952 --> 01:27:30,412
Are you crazy or what?

1201
01:27:31,038 --> 01:27:33,165
Natalia, behind you!

1202
01:27:37,044 --> 01:27:39,088
No!

1203
01:27:42,591 --> 01:27:44,426
No!

1204
01:27:45,427 --> 01:27:47,221
<i>Ray, where are you?</i>

1205
01:27:47,304 --> 01:27:50,057
- Down the tunnel ahead of you.
- Deni.

1206
01:27:52,101 --> 01:27:53,102
No.

1207
01:27:53,435 --> 01:27:55,145
Dad, I'm sorry!

1208
01:27:55,229 --> 01:27:57,106
I'm sorry!

1209
01:27:57,189 --> 01:27:58,357
Shut up.

1210
01:27:58,440 --> 01:28:00,859
Stop. Stop. Dad, please stop!

1211
01:28:02,778 --> 01:28:04,863
- Shut up.
- Please stop.

1212
01:28:09,451 --> 01:28:10,452
Ray!

1213
01:28:10,536 --> 01:28:13,038
Listen. They kidnapped you
and Deni from the hospital.

1214
01:28:13,122 --> 01:28:15,517
They beat the shit out of you.
They brought you here. Got it?

1215
01:28:15,541 --> 01:28:17,918
They kidnapped you and beat
the shit out of you. Got it?

1216
01:28:18,002 --> 01:28:20,170
- Ray?!
- You understand? I'm sorry.

1217
01:28:20,254 --> 01:28:22,172
- We're good.
- Good?

1218
01:28:22,256 --> 01:28:24,883
Yeah. We're good. Yeah.

1219
01:28:24,967 --> 01:28:26,802
Deni! Are you okay?

1220
01:28:31,098 --> 01:28:32,933
What happened?

1221
01:28:33,475 --> 01:28:36,270
Um... They um...

1222
01:28:38,605 --> 01:28:41,775
They... They beat the shit
out of me and Deni.

1223
01:28:41,859 --> 01:28:44,903
Kidnapped us from the hospital
and brought us here.

1224
01:28:47,865 --> 01:28:50,868
- Are you okay?
- Yeah, Mom, I'm okay.

1225
01:28:58,500 --> 01:29:01,253
I love you, Cody. I love you, son.

1226
01:29:02,921 --> 01:29:05,883
